        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:45PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Lindale, or 8 miles
southeast of Rome, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rome, Cartersville, Euharlee, Kingston, Taylorsville, Cassville,
Seney, and Lindale.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
